alert.note: Alert for Cook (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Advisory issued May 09 at 2:36PM CDT until May 14 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM CDT WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Minor flooding caused by rain and snowmelt continues. * WHERE...A portion of northeast Minnesota, including the following county, Cook. * WHEN...Until 400 PM CDT Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. River or stream flows are elevated. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 229 PM CDT Tuesday, gauge reports indicated elevated stream flows due to snow melt. Minor flooding is expected in the advisory area. - Visitors exploring area rivers for waterfall viewing or water recreation should use caution along waterways. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Temperance River State Park, Lutsen, Cascade River State Park, Grand Marais, Judge C.R. Magney State Park, and Grand Portage. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Keep children and pets close and under control. Strong river currents can sweep children away. Do not attempt to cross flooded roads. Find an alternate route. Hikers should avoid flooded trail crossings.
